The code below simulates a program that does NOTHING (Effect is 0). However, we will test it 100 times. How many times will we get a “Significant” result just by luck?
```gkxiteta set.seed(99) p_values &lt;- numeric(100)
for(i in 1:100) { # Generate two identical groups (No real difference) group_A &lt;- rnorm(30) group_B &lt;- rnorm(30)
# Run t-test and save p-value p_values[i] &lt;- t.test(group_A, group_B)$p.value }
